I changed the paragraph with the Grundrisse quote ("Marx himself said..."). Marx didn't say abstract labour existed in all societies, he said the abstraction "labour" existed in all societies. It's not the same thing. Abstract labour refers to the social objectivity of a commodity, as opposed to concrete labour, which forms the body of the commodity. The Grundrisse passage this refers to is concerned with quite different things.
